bsite=vstt.lt|access-date=2018-04-27|archive-date=2019-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191020225309/http://www.vstt.lt/VI/index.php#r/13|dead-url=no}}</ref>、402座[[自然保護區|自然保護區]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Draustiniai|url=http://www.vstt.lt/VI/index.php#r/10|website=vstt.lt|access-date=2021-06-27|archive-date=2019-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191020225309/http://www.vstt.lt/VI/index.php#r/10|dead-url=no}}</ref>與668個受國家保護的自然遺產<ref>{{cite web|title=Apie gamtos paveldo objektus|url=http://www.vstt.lt/VI/index.php#r/159|website=vstt.lt|access-date=2018-04-27|archive-date=2019-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191020225309/http://www.vstt.lt/VI/index.php#r/159|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

立陶宛獨立後，於1992年通過環境保護法（{{lang|lt|Aplinkos apsaugos įstatymas}}），規範個人（含[[法人|法人]]）對環境資源的使用，以保護國內的生物多樣性、生態系統與地貌<ref>{{cite web|title=Aplinkos apsaugos įstatymas|url=https://www.e-tar.lt/portal/lt/legalAct/TAR.E2780B68DE62/vsPTFQpUEB|website=e-tar.lt|access-date=2018-04-27|archive-date=2018-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180428011804/https://www.e-tar.lt/portal/lt/legalAct/TAR.E2780B68DE62/vsPTFQpUEB|dead-url=no}}</ref>。立陶宛與其他歐盟成員國皆同意在2020年將[[溫室氣體排放|碳排放]]減低至1990年的80%以下，將[[可再生能源|可再生能源]]占比提升至20%以上，並在2030年將碳排放進一步減低至1990年的60%以下，將可再生能源佔比提升至27%以上<ref>{{cite web|title=EU climate action|url=https://ec.europa.eu/clima/citizens/eu_en|website=European Commission|access-date=2018-04-27|date=2016-11-23|archive-date=2021-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210522200534/https://ec.europa.eu/clima/citizens/eu_en|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年立陶宛通過{{le|飲料瓶回收法|container deposit legislation}}，隔年成功回收了該年度92%的飲料瓶罐<ref>{{cite web|title=Europa suskubo paskui Lietuvą: kuo skiriasi šalių užstato sistemos?|url=https://www.15min.lt/naujiena/aktualu/lietuva/europa-suskubo-paskui-lietuva-kuo-skiriasi-saliu-uzstato-sistemos-56-968940|website=15min.lt|access-date=2018-05-09|archive-date=2021-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210623222136/https://www.15min.lt/naujiena/aktualu/lietuva/europa-suskubo-paskui-lietuva-kuo-skiriasi-saliu-uzstato-sistemos-56-968940|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2018年立陶宛在{{le|氣候變遷績效指標|Climate Change Performance Index}}的排名僅次於[[瑞典|瑞典]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Climate Change Performance Index 2018|url=https://www.climate-change-performance-index.org|website=Climate-change-performance-index.org|access-date=2018-05-14|archive-date=2018-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703224204/https://www.climate-change-performance-index.org/|dead-url=no}}</ref>；2019年立陶宛的{{le|森林景观完整性指数|Forest Landscape Integrity Index}}在172國中排名第162<ref name="FLII-Supplementary">{{cite journal|last1=Grantham|first1=H. S.|last2=Duncan|first2=A.|last3=Evans|first3=T. D.|last4=Jones|first4=K. R.|last5=Beyer|first5=H. L.|last6=Schuster|first6=R.|last7=Walston|first7=J.|last8=Ray|first8=J. C.|last9=Robinson|first9=J. G.|last10=Callow|first10=M.|last11=Clements|first11=T.|last12=Costa|first12=H. M.|last13=DeGemmis|first13=A.|last14=Elsen|first14=P. R.|last15=Ervin|first15=J.|last16=Franco|first16=P.|last17=Goldman|first17=E.|last18=Goetz|first18=S.|last19=Hansen|first19=A.|last20=Hofsvang|first20=E.|last21=Jantz|first21=P.|last22=Jupiter|first22=S.|last23=Kang|first23=A.|last24=Langhammer|first24=P.|last25=Laurance|first25=W. F.|last26=Lieberman|first26=S.|last27=Linkie|first27=M.|last28=Malhi|first28=Y.|last29=Maxwell|first29=S.|last30=Mendez|first30=M.|last31=Mittermeier|first31=R.|last32=Murray|first32=N. J.|last33=Possingham|first33=H.|last34=Radachowsky|first34=J.|last35=Saatchi|first35=S.|last36=Samper|first36=C.|last37=Silverman|first37=J.|last38=Shapiro|first38=A.|last39=Strassburg|first39=B.|last40=Stevens|first40=T.|last41=Stokes|first41=E.|last42=Taylor|first42=R.|last43=Tear|first43=T.|last44=Tizard|first44=R.|last45=Venter|first45=O.|last46=Visconti|first46=P.|last47=Wang|first47=S.|last48=Watson|first48=J. E. M.|title=Anthropogenic modification of forests means only 40% of remaining forests have high ecosystem integrity - Supplementary Material|journal=Nature Communications|volume=11|issue=1|year=2020|page=5978|issn=2041-1723|doi=10.1038/s