===健康===
[[File:Kauno_klinikos_2006_07_23.jpg|thumb]]
2019年立陶宛的[[平均壽命|平均壽命]]為76歲（男性71.2歲、女性80.4歲）<ref>{{cite web|title=Life expectancy and Healthy life expectancy, data by country|language=en|publisher=World Health Organization|url=https://apps.who.int/gho/data/node.main.688|date=2020|access-date=2021-07-14|archive-date=2013-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130305150130/https://apps.who.int/gho/data/node.main.688|dead-url=no}}</ref> ，[[嬰兒死亡率|嬰兒死亡率]]為2.99/千人<ref>{{cite web|title=Infant mortality rate - Total|publisher=[[UN|UN]] Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation|url=https://childmortality.org/data/Lithuania}}{{Dead link|date=May 2021 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> 。國內的{{le|立陶宛自殺現象|Suicide in Lithuania|高自殺率}}是一社會議題，1990年代自殺率大幅上升<ref name="who-suicide-data">{{cite web|title=Suicide rates. Data by country|url=http://apps.who.int/gho/data/node.main.MHSUICIDE?lang=en|publisher=World Health Organization|access-date=2016-09-07|archive-date=2015-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626141542/http://apps.who.int/gho/data/node.main.MHSUICIDE?lang=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>，後來雖逐年下降，但仍是歐盟國家中自殺率位居前列者<ref name="smhc-info">{{cite web|title=Savižudybių statistika|language=lt|publisher=State Mental Health Centre|url=https://vpsc.lrv.lt/lt/statistika/savizudybiu-statistika|access-date=2021-07-14|archive-date=2021-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210623221541/https://vpsc.lrv.lt/lt/statistika/savizudybiu-statistika|dead-url=no}}</ref>，2019年自殺率為20.2/10萬人<ref name="who-suicide-data"/>，自殺現象可能與社會轉型、經濟危機、酗酒、社會包容與霸凌有關<ref name="lrt-suicide-reasons">{{cite web|title=Pradeda veikti Savižudybių prevencijos biuras|date=2015-01-05|access-date=2021-05-19|publisher=Lithuanian Radio and Television|language=lt|url=https://www.lrt.lt/naujienos/tavo-lrt/15/88217/pradeda-veikti-savizudybiu-prevencijos-biuras|archive-date=2021-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210623221809/https://www.lrt.lt/naujienos/tavo-lrt/15/88217/pradeda-veikti-savizudybiu-prevencijos-biuras|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

{{tsl|en|Taxation in Lithuania|立陶宛稅制}}中包含強制的[[醫療保險|醫療保險]]（{{lang|lt|Privalomasis sveikatos draudimas}}，PSD）<ref>{{cite web|title=Compulsory Health Insurance Contributions|url=http://www.vlk.lt/sites/en/health-insurance-in-Lithuania/compulsory-health-insurance-contributions/|publisher=VLK|access-date=2015-07-03|archive-date=2021-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227080202/http://www.vlk.lt/sites/en/health-insurance-in-Lithuania/compulsory-health-insurance-contributions/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，涵蓋了包括[[急診|急診]]等大多數的醫療費用<ref>{{cite web|title=Accessing healthcare in Lithuania|url=http://www.nhs.uk/NHSEngland/Healthcareabroad/countryguide/Pages/healthcareinLithuania.aspx|website=NHS Choices|access-date=2015-07-03|archive-date=2018-04-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180401005245/https://www.nhs.uk/NHSEngland/Healthcareabroad/countryguide/Pages/healthcareinLithuania.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>（但不包括牙科、門診藥與部分醫療產品的費用<ref name=euro.who>{{cite news |title=Can people afford to pay for health care? |url=http://www.euro.who.int/__data/assets/pdf_file/0005/372425/ltu-fp-report-eng.pdf |access-date=2018-12-08 |publisher=WHO |date=2018 |archive-date=2021-07-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210720061726/https://www.euro.who.int/__data/assets/pdf_file/0005/372425/ltu-fp-report-eng.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>），且未納保者亦可使用免費急診服務<ref name=euro.who/>。2000年起立陶宛多數的醫療院所為非營利機構，除[[立陶宛衛生部|衛生部]]經營的數間醫院以外，也有許多私立醫院提供[[自付費用|自費]]門診服務<ref>{{cite book|title=Health Care Systems in Transition|date=2000|publisher=WHO|url=http://www.euro.who.int/__data/assets/pdf_file/0006/95127/E69920.pdf?ua=1|access-date=2015-07-03|archive-date=2021-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227035833/https://www.euro.who.int/__data/assets/pdf_file/0006/95127/E69920.pdf?ua=1|dead-url=no}}</ref>，醫療費用與其他歐洲國家相比較為低廉<ref>{{cite book|title=Comparing Hospital and Health Prices and Volumes Internationally|date=2014-08-06|publisher=[[Eurostat|Eurostat]]|page=28|url=http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/documents/728703/728971/OECD-health-working-papers-75.pdf/a6e22472-95c4-4e77-bdb0-db3af4668e7f|access-date=2021-07-14|archive-date=2021-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501013353/https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/documents/728703/728971/OECD-health-working-papers-75.pdf/a6e22472-95c4-4e77-bdb0-db3af4668e7f|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2009年統計全國有12,191名醫師（36.14名醫師/十萬人）<ref>{{cite news|title=Lithuania|url=https://www.who.int/countries/ltu/en/|access-date=2015-07-03|publisher=World Health Organization|archive-date=2020-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200902223353/https://www.who.int/countries/ltu/en/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2018年衡量歐洲各國醫療品質的{{le|歐洲健康消費指數|Euro Health Consumer Index}}中，立陶宛在35個國家中排名第28名<ref>{{cite web| url=https://healthpowerhouse.com/media/EHCI-2018/EHCI-2018-report.pdf| title=Euro Health Consumer Index 2018| publisher=Health Consumer Powerhouse| access-date=2019-02-26| archive-date=2020-11-12| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112031255/https://healthpowerhouse.com/media/EHCI-2018/EHCI-2018-report.pdf| dead-url=no}}</ref>。

一项来自牛津大学的研究表明，[[2019冠状病毒病疫情|2019冠状病毒病疫情]]导致了立陶宛男性预期寿命降低了1.7岁（在研究的29个国家中仅次于美国的2.2岁），女性则降低了1.3岁。<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Jose Manuel Aburto, et al. |title=Quantifying impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic through life-expectancy losses: a population-level study of 29 countries |journal=International Journal of Epidemioligy |date=2021-09-26 |doi=10.1093/ije/dyab207 |url=https://academic.oup.com/ije/advance-article/doi/10.1093/ije/dyab207/6375510#304303699 |accessdate=2021-09-29 |archive-date=2021-10-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211031015356/https://academic.oup.com/ije/advance-article/doi/10.1093/ije/dyab207/6375510#304303699 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

===教育===
[[File:Vytautas_Magnus_University,_2016.jpg|thumb]]人文學院與政治外交學院大樓]]
立陶宛憲法規定國民6歲至16歲需接受十年的[[義務教育|義務教育]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Constitution of the Republic of Lithuania came into force on 2 November 1992|url=http://www3.lrs.lt/home/Konstitucija/Constitution.htm|access-date=2010-04-06|publisher=Republic of Lithuania|archive-date=2016-01-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160101054453/http://www3.lrs.lt/home/Konstitucija/Constitution.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年政府在{{tsl|en|Education in Lithuania|立陶宛教育|教育}}上的花費約合GDP的5.4%（公共支出總和的15.4%）<ref name=edumonitor>{{cite web|title=Education and Training Monitor 2017. Lithuania|url=https://ec.europa.eu/education/sites/education/files/monitor2017-lt_en.pdf|access-date=2018-04-05|page=3|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180406041020/https://ec.europa.eu/education/sites/education/files/monitor2017-lt_en.pdf|archive-date=2018-04-06|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。[[維爾紐斯大學|維爾紐斯大學]]是立陶宛最大的大學，且為歐洲歷史最悠久的大學之一，其歷史可追溯至1579年<ref name=VU1579/>；[[考納斯理工大學|考納斯理工大學]]為立陶宛排名第二的大學，為波羅的海地區重要的理工大學<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2018-05/09/c_137167486.htm|title=Vilnius University ranked top Lithuanian state university|date=2018-05-09|publisher=Xinhuanet|access-date=2021-07-15|archive-date=2021-07-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210719075206/http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2018-05/09/c_137167486.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[File:GreatCourtyard.jpg|thumb]]的歷史可追溯至1579年<ref name=VU1579>{{cite web|title=FOUR CENTURIES OF ENLIGHTENMENT: A Historic View of the University of Vilnius, 1579–1979|url=http://www.lituanus.org/1981_2/81_2_01.htm|author=Tomas Venclova|website=Lituanus.org|access-date=2018-06-02|archive-date=2021-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210623222449/http://www.lituanus.org/1981_2/81_2_01.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>]]

[[世界銀行|世界銀行]]統計立陶宛15歲以上人口的[[識字率|識字率]]為100%<ref>{{cite web |title=ICT at a Glance |url=http://devdata.worldbank.org/ict/ltu_ict.pdf |publisher=[[World_Bank|World Bank]] |access-date=2010-04-07 |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070707184435/http://devdata.worldbank.org/ict/ltu_ict.pdf |archive-date=2007-07-07 }}</ref>，入學率高於歐盟平均，失學率也低於歐盟平均，歐洲統計局資料顯示立陶宛人受過中等教育者的比例在歐盟國家中位居前列<ref>{{cite web|title=Upper secondary education in EU|url=http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/tgm/table.do?tab=table&plugin=1&language=en&pcode=tps00065|publisher=[[Eurostat|Eurostat]]|access-date=2014-05-16|archive-date=2014-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140517120812/http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/tgm/table.do?tab=table&plugin=1&language=en&pcode=tps00065|dead-url=no}}</ref> ，[[經濟合作暨發展組織|經濟合作暨發展組織]]（OECD）數據顯示立陶宛人接受[[第三期教育|中學後教育]]的比例位居世界前五<ref>{{cite web|title=Population with tertiary education|url=https://data.oecd.org/eduatt/population-with-tertiary-education.htm|website=data.oecd.org|access-date=2018-11-17|archive-date=2019-09-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925040912/https://data.oecd.org/eduatt/population-with-tertiary-education.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，2016年25至34歲的人口中有54.9%已完成中學後教育，25至64歲人口中完成[[理工科|理工科]]、商科、行政與法律中學後教育者皆略高於OECD國家的平均值<ref>{{cite web|title=Education at a glance 2017. Lithuania|url=http://gpseducation.oecd.org/Content/EAGCountryNotes/LTU.pdf|website=gpseducation.oecd.org|page=2|access-date=2018-04-04|archive-date=2019-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808021023/http://gpseducation.oecd.org/Content/EAGCountryNotes/LTU.pdf|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

立陶宛的教育系統也面臨一些結構性議題，例如資金不足、教學品質不佳與學生數量下降等，立陶宛教師的薪資是歐盟國家中最低的<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.delfi.lt/news/ringas/politics/m-adomenas-lietuvos-svietimas-ka-daryciau-kitaip.d?id=71141632|title=M. Adomėnas. Lietuvos švietimas: ką daryčiau kitaip?|first=Mantas Adomėnas, TS-LKD frakcijos narys|last=Seime|website=Delfi.lt|access-date=2018-01-04|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417180635/https://www.delfi.lt/news/ringas/politics/m-adomenas-lietuvos-svietimas-ka-daryciau-kitaip.d?id=71141632|dead-url=no}}</ref>，2014年<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.delfi.lt/news/daily/education/mokyklose-prasideda-neterminuotas-mokytoju-streikas.d?id=66552496|title=Mokyklose prasideda neterminuotas mokytojų streikas|website=Delfi.lt|access-date=2018-01-04|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417193855/https://www.delfi.lt/news/daily/education/mokyklose-prasideda-neterminuotas-mokytoju-streikas.d?id=66552496|dead-url=no}}</ref>、2015年<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ve.lt/naujienos/visuomene/svietimas/mokytoju-streikas-pavyko-1419148/|title=Mokytojų streikas pavyko|website=Dienraštis Vakaru ekspresas|access-date=2018-01-04|archive-date=2021-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210511221339/https://ve.lt/naujienos/visuomene/svietimas/mokytoju-streikas-pavyko-1419148|dead-url=no}}</ref>與2016年<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.15min.lt/naujiena/aktualu/svietimas/mokytoju-streikas-svarbiausi-faktai-233-591297|title=Mokytojų streikas: svarbiausi faktai|website=15min.lt|access-date=2018-01-04|archive-date=2021-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210623222404/https://www.15min.lt/naujiena/aktualu/svietimas/mokytoju-streikas-svarbiausi-faktai-233-591297|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.15min.lt/naujiena/aktualu/svietimas/mokytoju-streikas-tesiasi-110-ugdymo-istaigu-233-590739|title=Mokytojų streikas tęsiasi 110 ugdymo įstaigų|website=15min.lt|access-date=2018-01-04|archive-date=2021-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210623222223/https://www.15min.lt/naujiena/aktualu/svietimas/mokytoju-streikas-tesiasi-110-ugdymo-istaigu-233-590739|dead-url=no}}</ref>皆導致教師罷工抗議，高等教育教師的薪資也較低落，許多大學教授需兼職以維生<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tv3.lt/naujiena/934883/lietuvos-destytojai-bei-mokslininkai-atvirai-prabilo-kaip-prisiduria-prie-algos|title=Lietuvos dėstytojai bei mokslininkai atvirai prabilo, kaip prisiduria prie algos|website=Tv3.lt|access-date=2018-01-04|archive-date=2020-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201031153254/https://www.tv3.lt/naujiena/934883/lietuvos-destytojai-bei-mokslininkai-atvirai-prabilo-kaip-prisiduria-prie-algos|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[國際學生能力評估計劃|國際學生能力評估計劃]]（PISA）2010年與2015年的報告中，立陶宛學生的數學、科學與閱讀能力皆低於OECD國家平均<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oecd.org/pisa/pisaproducts/46619703.pdf|title=PISA 2009 Results : Executive Summary|website=Oecd.org|access-date=2018-10-18|archive-date=2021-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210516195314/https://www.oecd.org/pisa/pisaproducts/46619703.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oecd.org/pisa/pisa-2015-results-in-focus.pdf|title=Pisa 2015 : Results in Focus|website=Oecd.org|access-date=2018-10-18|archive-date=2019-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190930042816/https://www.oecd.org/pisa/pisa-2015-results-in-focus.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。從2005年到2015年，少子化造成6至19歲的人口數下降了36%，使得學校的[[師生比|師生比]]提高，許多鄉村學校被迫重組整併<ref name=edumonitor/>，為因應少子化<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alfa.lt/straipsnis/12887651/universitetu-reforma-darbas-ant-durniaus|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180113151138/https://www.alfa.lt/straipsnis/12887651/universitetu-reforma-darbas-ant-durniaus|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2018-01-13|title=Alfa.lt – Universitetų reforma – "darbas ant durniaus"|date=2018-01-13|access-date=2021-07-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ve.lt/naujienos/visuomene/svietimas/pristatyta-aukstuju-mokyklu-tinklo-pertvarka-1550590/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180113151028/http://www.ve.lt/naujienos/visuomene/svietimas/pristatyta-aukstuju-mokyklu-tinklo-pertvarka-1550590/|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2018-01-13|title=Pristatyta aukštųjų mokyklų tinklo pertvarka|date=2018-01-13|access-date=2021-07-15}}</ref>，立陶宛議會決議減少大專院校的數量<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diena.lt/naujienos/lietuva/salies-pulsas/vyriausybe-pritare-universitetu-pertvarkos-planui-838745|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180113151301/http://www.diena.lt/naujienos/lietuva/salies-pulsas/vyriausybe-pritare-universitetu-pertvarkos-planui-838745|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2018-01-13|title=Vyriausybė pritarė universitetų pertvarkos planui – Diena.lt|date=2018-01-13|access-date=2021-07-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.delfi.lt/news/daily/lithuania/seimas-po-svarstymo-pritare-valstybiniu-universitetu-pertvarkos-planui.d?id=75022448|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180113151333/https://www.delfi.lt/news/daily/lithuania/seimas-po-svarstymo-pritare-valstybiniu-universitetu-pertvarkos-planui.d?id=75022448|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2018-01-13|title=Seimas po svarstymo pritarė valstybinių universitetų pertvarkos planui – DELFI|date=2018-01-13|access-date=2021-07-15}}</ref>，例如在2018年將{{le|立陶宛教育大學|Lithuanian University of Educational Sciences}}與{{le|維陶塔斯馬格努斯大學農學院|Vytautas Magnus University Agriculture Academy|亞歷山德拉斯·斯圖爾金斯基斯大學}}併入[[維陶塔斯馬格努斯大學|維陶塔斯馬格努斯大學]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.delfi.lt/news/daily/education/seimas-pritare-3-universitetu-sujungimui-formuojamas-naujas-darinys.d?id=76893227|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180113152341/https://www.delfi.lt/news/daily/education/seimas-pritare-3-universitetu-sujungimui-formuojamas-naujas-darinys.d?id=76893227|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2018-01-13|title=Seimas pritarė 3 universitetų sujungimui: formuojamas naujas darinys – DELFI|date=2018-01-13|access-date=2021-07-15}}</ref>。

立陶宛也與鄰國拉脫維亞同樣面臨受高等教育的雙語者[[人才外流|人才外流]]至他國的問題<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-31488046|title=Can Lithuania turn brain drain into brain gain?|publisher=BBC News|author=Nic Mitchell|date=2015-02-18|access-date=2021-07-15|archive-date=2021-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210720064315/https://www.bbc.com/news/business-31488046|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 基礎建設 ==
===交通運輸===
{{main|立陶宛交通}}
[[File:Lithuania-roads-(E).png|thumb]]
運輸業是立陶宛經濟中排行第三的產業<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sumin.lrv.lt/en/news/lithuania-is-ready-to-implement-transport-investment-projects-of-a-strategic-importance|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180104145320/https://sumin.lrv.lt/en/news/lithuania-is-ready-to-implement-transport-investment-projects-of-a-strategic-importance|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2018-01-04|title=Lithuania is ready to implement transport investment project of a strategic importance – Ministry of Transport and Communications|date=2018-01-04|access-date=2021-07-15}}</ref>。經過立陶宛的第一條鐵路為{{tsl|en|Warsaw – Saint Petersburg Railway|華沙-聖彼得堡鐵路}}，始建於19世紀中葉，當時建造的[[考那斯鐵路隧道|考那斯鐵路隧道]]現仍在使用<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.litrail.lt/wps/portal/!ut/p/c1/04_SB8K8xLLM9MSSzPy8xBz9CP0os3h3C2N_VzcPIwMDH3NHAyNTU69gPyd_QycnY6B8JE554yBjArrDQfbhVOHlb4xXHmw-PvkQQ4i8AQ7gaKDv55Gfm6ofnJqnX5AbYZDpqesIAMGhx7A!/dl2/d1/L2dJQSEvUUt3QS9ZQnB3LzZfRzgzT0VGSDIwMEw3QTAyNTVKU05CTzFCQjM!/|title=Lithuanian Railways: From Province of Tsarist Russia to European Transport Market|publisher=litrail.lt|access-date=2021-07-15|archive-date=2012-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120303202355/http://www.litrail.lt/wps/portal/!ut/p/c1/04_SB8K8xLLM9MSSzPy8xBz9CP0os3h3C2N_VzcPIwMDH3NHAyNTU69gPyd_QycnY6B8JE554yBjArrDQfbhVOHlb4xXHmw-PvkQQ4i8AQ7gaKDv55Gfm6ofnJqnX5AbYZDpqesIAMGhx7A!/dl2/d1/L2dJQSEvUUt3QS9ZQnB3LzZfRzgzT0VGSDIwMEw3QTAyNTVKU05CTzFCQjM!/|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fima.lt/index.php/site_structure/news/55;year;2009|title=Fima's Engineering Solutions Make Kaunas Tunnel Safer|access-date=2021-07-15|archive-date=2012-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120326115020/http://www.fima.lt/index.php/site_structure/news/55;year;2009|dead-url=no}}</ref>。現時[[立陶宛鐵路|立陶宛鐵路]]路網長約1,700公里，使用[[俄罗斯轨距|俄罗斯轨距]]（其中有115公里使用[[標準軌|標準軌]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Geležinkelių infrastruktūra|url=http://infrastructure.litrail.lt/|website=Infrastructure.litrail.lt|access-date=2017-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171006220502/http://infrastructure.litrail.lt/|archive-date=2017-10-06|dead-url=yes}}</ref>），其中約120公里已電氣化，因多數鐵道軌距與歐洲其他國家的標準軌不同，運行時需要換軌。立陶宛國內超過一半的貨運使用鐵路<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/statistics-explained/index.php/Freight_transport_statistics|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180104135126/http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/statistics-explained/index.php/Freight_transport_statistics|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2018-01-04|title=Freight transport statistics – Statistics Explained|date=2018-01-04|access-date=2018-01-04}}</ref>。連接[[芬蘭|芬蘭]]與波蘭的標準軌鐵路[[波羅的海鐵路|波羅的海鐵路]]現正興建中，將穿越立陶宛等波羅的海國家<ref name="feasibility EU">{{cite web |url=http://ec.europa.eu/regional_policy/sources/docgener/evaluation/railbaltica/concl_en.PDF |title=Feasibility study on Rail Baltica railways |date=January 2007 |author=European Commission, Directorate-General for Regional Policy |access-date=2021-07-15 |archive-date=2012-01-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120113040231/http://ec.europa.eu/regional_policy/sources/docgener/evaluation/railbaltica/concl_en.PDF |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

