立陶宛過去高度依賴[[核能发电|核能发电]]，据[[国际原子能机构|国际原子能机构]]统计，2002年底立陶宛的核能发电在全国总发电比例中占了80.1%<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iaea.org/newscenter/pressreleases/iaea-releases-nuclear-power-statistics-2002|title=IAEA Releases Nuclear Power Statistics For 2002|publisher=IAEA|date=2003-09|access-date=2021-07-15|archive-date=2021-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210720062346/https://www.iaea.org/newscenter/pressreleases/iaea-releases-nuclear-power-statistics-2002|dead-url=no}}</ref>，當時立陶宛的核能發電廠[[伊格納利納核電站|伊格納利納核電站]]反應爐的設計與發生事故的[[車諾比核電廠|車諾比核電廠]]類似，且一樣缺乏穩固的[[核反应堆安全壳|安全殼]]<ref>{{cite book|title=Transboundary risk management|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AEM1GMPGQk0C&pg=PA35|page=35|last1=Linnerooth-Bayer|first1=Joanne|author2-link=Ragnar Löfstedt|last2=Löfstedt|first2=Ragnar|last3=Sjöstedt|first3=Gunnar|publisher={{tsl|en|Earthscan|}}|year=2001|isbn=978-1-85383-537-7|access-date=2009-12-31|archive-date=2021-08-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210806165622/https://books.google.com/books?id=AEM1GMPGQk0C&pg=PA35|dead-url=no}}</ref>，歐盟將關閉此核電廠作為立陶宛入盟的條件，2004年底立陶宛將一號機關閉，2009年底又將二號機關閉<ref name=nea>{{cite book |title=Nuclear legislation in Central and Eastern Europe and the NIS: 2003 overview |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NHscLfB64EwC&pg=PA116 |page=116 |publisher=[[经济合作与发展组织|经济合作与发展组织]] |year=2004 |isbn=978-92-64-01542-5 |access-date=2009-12-31 |author=Nuclear Energy Agency, Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development. |archive-date=2021-07-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210720062346/https://books.google.com/books?id=NHscLfB64EwC&pg=PA116 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="BBC">{{cite news |title=Lithuania to shut its only nuclear power station |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/8435628.stm |work=BBC News |date=2009-12-31 |access-date=2009-12-31 |archive-date=2022-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220417060319/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/8435628.stm }}</ref><ref name=businessweek>{{cite news |title=Lithuania shuts down Soviet-built nuclear reactor |url=http://www.businessweek.com/ap/financialnews/D9CUCPIO0.htm |publisher=[[彭博有限合夥企業|彭博有限合夥企業]] |author=Dapkus, Liudas |work=[[彭博商业周刊|彭博商业周刊]] |date=2009-12-31 |access-date=2009-12-31 |archive-date=2010-01-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100104144655/http://www.businessweek.com/ap/financialnews/D9CUCPIO0.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>，原本計劃興建的[[維薩吉納斯核電站|維薩吉納斯核電站]]也於{{tsl|en|2012 Lithuanian nuclear power referendum|2012年立陶宛核能發電公投|2012年公投}}中因近65%的投票者反對而被叫停<ref>{{cite web|title=2012 m. Lietuvos Respublikos Seimo rinkimai ir referendumas dėl naujos atominės elektrinės statybos Lietuvos Respublikoje|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016192607/http://www.vrk.lt/2012_seimo_rinkimai/output_lt/referendumas/referendumas.html|publisher=Lietuvos Respublikos vyriausioji rinkimų komisija|date=2012-10}}</ref><ref name=baltic-course-20160413>{{cite news |url=http://www.baltic-course.com/eng/energy/?doc=119397 |title=Lithuania's ex-minister: Visaginas NPP plant project dead |website=The Baltic Course |date=2016-04-13 |access-date=2018-02-17 |archive-date=2018-02-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180217203104/http://www.baltic-course.com/eng/energy/?doc=119397 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-nuclear.org/info/Country-Profiles/Countries-G-N/Lithuania/|title=Nuclear Power in Lithuania – Lithuanian Nuclear Energy – World Nuclear Association|website=World-nuclear.org|access-date=2018-10-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126160031/http://www.world-nuclear.org/info/Country-Profiles/Countries-G-N/Lithuania/|archive-date=2016-01-26|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。
